Rough working, similar to page 14 of the 'Magisteria' (Add MS 6782

f. 121
).

This page contains jottings on both binary and ternary arithmetic. 

The calculation on the left shows 101101 (= 45) multiplied by 1011 (= 11);
the answer, 111,101,111 (= 495), is then divided by 1011 (= 11) to recover 101101 (= 45).
